@NODE formats "All that I know..."
@TOC docs

                             @{fg highlight}KNOWN SAMPLE FORMATS@{fg text}

 @{b}1. IFF-8SVX (8 bit MONO):@{ub} This is one of the  most used  sample  formats on
                           the amiga. It  provides, as all  IFF-formats  do,
                           the  possibility  to store  data  in own  defined
    @{fg highlight}LOAD/SAVE@{fg text}              chunks. Sample  Editor  does  so  with  adding  a
                           "MARK" chunk, in  which it  stores the start  and
                           end marks of the sample when set.

 @{b}2. RAW DATA (8 bit MONO):@{ub} This is currently the most used sample format. It
                           consists  only  of  the  bare  sample  wave  data
    @{fg highlight}LOAD/SAVE@{fg text}              without  any  further  information like  playback
                           speed, marker positions etc.

 @{b}3. WAVE     (8 bit MONO):@{ub} On MS-DOS machines  (Intel outside ;-) the ruling
                           standard for storing samples. I included this for
    @{fg highlight}LOAD ONLY@{fg text}              easy converting  of PC-Samples (look at those CD-
                           ROM libraries... 8-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE history "What's new since V1.0?"
@TOC docs

 @{fg highlight}V1.4 (03.11.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Uses at last the 'audio.device'. Double-Buffering reduced to 4 KB.

 @{fg highlight}V1.3a (28.10.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Makes use of the BevelBox.Library (included).
 - Doesn't use the VBeam anymore to prevent timig problems.
 - Flickering while range marking mostly removed.
 - Various optimisations in the source code.

 @{fg highlight}V1.3 (12.06.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Added ARexx-Port.
 - Fixed problem with CLI-Arguments.
 - Built in chorus effect.
 - Better handling of the HELP key.

 @{fg highlight}V1.3 (14.05.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Added keyboard commands F6, F7, F8, F9, F10, SPACE.
 - Removed bug with keyboard and samples >20kB.
 - Improved text placement in the windows.
 - Improved menu layout.
 - Included french .catalog file.
 - Added tiny buttons.

 @{fg highlight}V1.2 (16.03.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Spelling errors in German catalog corrected.

 @{fg highlight}V1.2 (21.02.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Added CLI-Arguments SAMPLEDIR=DIR, PATTERN=PAT and DOCVIEW=DOC.
 - Various smaller enhancements to the source code.
 - Improved gadget handling.
 - Sample monitor turned around.

 @{fg highlight}V1.2 (07.02.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Now supports the Locale.Library.
 - German catalog written.
 - German documentation written.
 - .keyfile may be stored in either the DEVS: L: S: ENV: or current drawer.

 @{fg highlight}V1.1 (13.01.1995)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Added ToolTypes SAMPLEDIR, PATTERN and DOCVIEW

 @{fg highlight}V1.1 (14.12.1994)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - Added gadgets for doubling/halving of the playback speed.
 - Sample Editor had some trouble  reading IFF-samples, if their chunks were
   not at LONG-Borders. This is now fixed.
 - Zoom Range is now able to be moved around.

 @{fg highlight}V1.0 (16.11.1994)
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
 - First beta-Release.
@ENDNODE

